[shutter clicks]

00:00:10.630 --> 00:00:13.220
[SAKAKI] And that's pretty
much how it went down.

00:00:13.300 --> 00:00:14.640
Who said you could take those?

00:00:14.720 --> 00:00:16.140
You gotta delete that right now!

00:00:16.220 --> 00:00:18.980
Something juicy happened when
I wasn't around to see it?

00:00:19.060 --> 00:00:21.350
You should've
called me right away!

00:00:21.440 --> 00:00:24.860
Sorry, it must've
just slipped my mind.

00:00:24.940 --> 00:00:27.070
[ASAI] You guys aren't
snubbing me, are you?

00:00:27.150 --> 00:00:28.570
No, nothing like that.

00:00:28.650 --> 00:00:30.200
We would never.

00:00:30.280 --> 00:00:31.530
Do you mean it?

00:00:31.610 --> 00:00:33.030
[UZAKI, SAKURAI]
Mm-hm.

00:00:33.120 --> 00:00:34.280
How 'bout we make it up to you

00:00:34.370 --> 00:00:36.290
and hang out all
together sometime?

00:00:36.370 --> 00:00:39.830
That sounds pretty good, right?
So, we cool?

00:00:42.040 --> 00:00:43.380
Totes cool!

00:00:43.460 --> 00:00:46.840
Long as I get front row seats
to the Sakuzaki show,

00:00:46.920 --> 00:00:48.550
I'm down to clown!

00:00:48.630 --> 00:00:51.590
[SAKAKI] Yeesh. Always
scheming, that one.

00:00:51.680 --> 00:00:53.640
[SAKAKI] Let's figure out
what we're doing then.

00:00:53.720 --> 00:00:54.850
[SAKURAI]
Good idea.

00:00:54.930 --> 00:00:57.930
[UZAKI] Ooh, I could use
some retail therapy!

00:00:58.020 --> 00:01:00.560
Ah, to be young again.

00:02:37.910 --> 00:02:39.950
Now that you're an
upperclassman, you barely even

00:02:40.030 --> 00:02:43.410
have to go to class, huh.
Must be nice.

00:02:43.500 --> 00:02:46.250
You'll be free soon,
so hang in there.

00:02:46.330 --> 00:02:49.340
Uzaki struggles when she
has to write an essay.

00:02:49.420 --> 00:02:52.130
Look, that stuff is a breeze
when I apply myself!

00:02:52.210 --> 00:02:53.470
I bet.

00:02:53.550 --> 00:02:56.050
Besides, I have tons of friends
who can tutor me.

00:02:56.130 --> 00:02:58.300
Unlike a certain
sweaty try-hard loner

00:02:58.390 --> 00:03:00.010
whose name rhymes
with pah-ku-pie!

00:03:00.100 --> 00:03:02.350
Then you won't be
needing me I suppose.

00:03:02.430 --> 00:03:06.350
Uh! Hey! That's against
the rules, you jerk!

00:03:06.440 --> 00:03:08.060
[SAKURAI]
What are you even talking about?

00:03:08.150 --> 00:03:11.400
It's your obligation as an
upperclassman to help me!

00:03:11.480 --> 00:03:14.280
[laughs] Well then, guess
he won't have to worry

00:03:14.360 --> 00:03:16.110
about getting one-upped
in academics.

00:03:16.200 --> 00:03:18.450
Ugh. I hardly see you, either.

00:03:18.530 --> 00:03:20.950
Are you even graduating
at this rate?

00:03:21.030 --> 00:03:23.200
You gonna get held back?

00:03:23.290 --> 00:03:24.580
[SAKURAI]
Heh. You kidding?

00:03:24.660 --> 00:03:26.000
That guy's got more
creds than I do.

00:03:26.080 --> 00:03:27.290
[gasps]

00:03:27.370 --> 00:03:29.210
[SAKURAI]
Itsuhito's something else.

00:03:29.290 --> 00:03:31.210
He registers for
easy classes where all

00:03:31.290 --> 00:03:33.130
he has to do is show up
once in a while

00:03:33.210 --> 00:03:35.470
and hand in a paper to pass.

00:03:35.550 --> 00:03:38.550
[ASAI] Some people just happen
to be gifted like that.

00:03:38.630 --> 00:03:41.300
Well you know what they say,
"work smarter not harder."

00:03:41.390 --> 00:03:42.560
Ah!

00:03:42.640 --> 00:03:44.180
[ASAI] What do you do
with all your free time?

00:03:44.260 --> 00:03:46.390
[SAKAKI]
Uh, I really like to go camping.

00:03:46.480 --> 00:03:48.730
[ASAI]
Ooh, that sounds nice!

00:03:48.810 --> 00:03:50.310
[UZAKI]
So not fair.

00:03:50.400 --> 00:03:54.400
[NARRATOR] It was a way of life
Uzaki had no hope of imitating.

00:03:56.030 --> 00:03:57.780
[UZAKI]
Wanna check out the swimsuits?

00:03:57.860 --> 00:03:59.200
[ASAI]
Let's go.

00:04:00.450 --> 00:04:02.700
[ASAI] Why do you need
another swimsuit, anyway?

00:04:02.780 --> 00:04:07.080
Because... I've been going to
the pool a lot more lately.

00:04:07.160 --> 00:04:08.040
[ASAI]
Have you?

00:04:08.120 --> 00:04:09.960
Yeah, with Sakurai.

00:04:10.040 --> 00:04:11.960
[ASAI]
I need details!

00:04:12.040 --> 00:04:14.000
[UZAKI] After we went to
the beach that one time,

00:04:14.090 --> 00:04:17.340
he's started being
more physically active.

00:04:23.220 --> 00:04:24.310
Here, take a look.

00:04:24.390 --> 00:04:28.690
[SAKURAI]
Thanks. Crap, my times suck.

00:04:28.770 --> 00:04:30.850
My swim club days are long gone.

00:04:30.940 --> 00:04:32.900
Listen, they may have
pool lanes here,

00:04:32.980 --> 00:04:35.820
but it doesn't mean you have
to act like it's a competition.

00:04:35.900 --> 00:04:38.240
[SAKURAI]
Sorry. Old habit.

00:04:38.320 --> 00:04:40.900
Okay, time for a relaxing dip!

00:04:40.990 --> 00:04:41.780
[UZAKI]
Right!

00:04:41.870 --> 00:04:43.780
[SAKURAI]
Oh, by the way.

00:04:43.870 --> 00:04:45.540
[UZAKI]
What?

00:04:45.620 --> 00:04:49.370
Cute swimsuit today...
today... today...

00:04:49.460 --> 00:04:52.710
[UZAKI gasping]

00:04:52.790 --> 00:04:54.040
Weird, right?

00:04:54.130 --> 00:04:56.550
Like, that compliment came
out of nowhere, ya know?

00:04:56.630 --> 00:04:59.920
But it felt nice, so I thought
I'd buy some more.

00:05:00.010 --> 00:05:01.970
[ASAI] Start with a
swimsuit compliment.

00:05:02.050 --> 00:05:03.930
Not mine, you idiot!

00:05:04.010 --> 00:05:06.970
Aha. The pupil
becomes the master.

00:05:07.060 --> 00:05:09.930
Pleased to hear my advice
is being put to use.

00:05:10.020 --> 00:05:12.350
[SAKURAI]
Let's see... A-choo!

00:05:12.440 --> 00:05:14.940
He probably didn't
mean anything by it...

00:05:15.020 --> 00:05:17.360
[ASAI]
Hana looks so happy right now.

00:05:17.440 --> 00:05:20.820
Why say anything that could
spoil the mood?

00:05:20.900 --> 00:05:23.110
I wish I'd got to see
her all embarrassed

00:05:23.200 --> 00:05:25.870
about her swimsuit
compliment! No fair!

00:05:25.950 --> 00:05:28.120
[BOY A]
Mom! She's crying blood!

00:05:29.370 --> 00:05:30.910
[UZAKI grunting]

00:05:31.000 --> 00:05:32.370
[SAKURAI grunts]

00:05:32.460 --> 00:05:33.880
[UZAKI grunting]

00:05:33.960 --> 00:05:36.340
[SAKURAI grunts]

00:05:36.420 --> 00:05:37.340
[grunts]

00:05:37.420 --> 00:05:39.460
[SAKURAI grunting]

00:05:39.550 --> 00:05:40.460
Ah!

00:05:40.550 --> 00:05:41.880
Here!

00:05:41.970 --> 00:05:43.550
[UZAKI]
C'mon, try to keep up!

00:05:43.630 --> 00:05:46.390
[SAKURAI] Could you not yell?
It's distracting!

00:05:46.470 --> 00:05:49.350
Atta boy. For a guy who says
he's totally hopeless

00:05:49.430 --> 00:05:50.600
when it comes to sports,

00:05:50.680 --> 00:05:53.060
he's actually warmed up
to this pretty quickly.

00:05:53.140 --> 00:05:55.020
Now just imagine how
"hot" stuff could get

00:05:55.110 --> 00:05:57.150
if something indecent
were to happen.

00:05:57.230 --> 00:05:59.690
This isn't really
that kinda game, Ami.

00:05:59.780 --> 00:06:02.110
[ASAI]
With some changes, it could be.

00:06:02.190 --> 00:06:04.610
[yelling]

00:06:04.700 --> 00:06:08.410
No! Not the no-no bits!

00:06:08.490 --> 00:06:10.330
Hey, you two down
for a mini-match?

00:06:10.410 --> 00:06:12.290
I'm not sure if
I'm ready for that.

00:06:12.370 --> 00:06:15.790
C'mon dude, it's only
for funsies. Just one game.

00:06:15.880 --> 00:06:17.210
Are you sure?

00:06:17.290 --> 00:06:19.460
Who'd expect anything
professional from you, anyway,

00:06:19.550 --> 00:06:20.800
so no pressure.

00:06:20.880 --> 00:06:23.050
They're totally
underestimating us here!

00:06:23.130 --> 00:06:26.260
No, I really do kinda suck.

00:06:26.340 --> 00:06:28.600
Shall we go ahead
and split into teams?

00:06:28.680 --> 00:06:29.890
[SASAMOTO laughing]

00:06:29.970 --> 00:06:31.140
[ALL]
Huh...?

00:06:31.220 --> 00:06:33.810
They can't even beat us
when it's 5 against 3!

00:06:33.890 --> 00:06:36.690
But do you expect from
a team of middle-schoolers?

00:06:36.770 --> 00:06:39.110
Whoa, ease up, bro!

00:06:39.190 --> 00:06:41.110
You jerks.

00:06:41.190 --> 00:06:42.440
What're they doing
playing against

00:06:42.530 --> 00:06:43.990
a bunch of little children?

00:06:44.070 --> 00:06:46.320
Pretty cringe if you ask me.

00:06:46.410 --> 00:06:48.570
Where do you old losers
get off messing with people

00:06:48.660 --> 00:06:50.950
half your age just for
the fun of it, huh?

00:06:51.040 --> 00:06:52.830
Don't you have a
lame college party

00:06:52.910 --> 00:06:54.290
or something to run off to?

00:06:54.370 --> 00:06:57.330
Aw boo-hoo, are the pathetic
overgrown varsity rejects

00:06:57.420 --> 00:06:59.670
upset that all the pretty
girls keep ghosting them?

00:06:59.750 --> 00:07:01.090
Cry me a river.

00:07:01.170 --> 00:07:02.800
--Booo!
--Booooo!

00:07:02.880 --> 00:07:04.880
They may be young,
but those middle-schoolers

00:07:04.970 --> 00:07:07.720
can dish it out as well
as they can take it.

00:07:08.930 --> 00:07:11.010
[NARRATOR]
It was highly effective.

00:07:11.100 --> 00:07:12.260
[SAKURAI]
They got owned.

00:07:12.350 --> 00:07:14.430
[ASAI]
I don't think I can watch this.

00:07:14.520 --> 00:07:16.350
[UZAKI]
Is that guy crying?

00:07:16.440 --> 00:07:20.060
Huh?! I'm not crying!
Besides, who the hell are you?

00:07:20.150 --> 00:07:21.320
Watch out! He's unhinged!

00:07:21.400 --> 00:07:23.820
I think he's just
talking loudly.

00:07:23.900 --> 00:07:27.780
Let's calm down. We both paid
good money to play here, right?

00:07:27.860 --> 00:07:30.870
How about we try to be a little
more mindful of the space?

00:07:30.950 --> 00:07:33.870
Wha--?! Wait,
it that you, Sakaki?

00:07:33.950 --> 00:07:35.080
[SAKAKI]
Huh?

00:07:35.160 --> 00:07:36.120
You know him?

00:07:36.210 --> 00:07:37.750
Uh, nope.

00:07:37.830 --> 00:07:39.830
Whaddaya mean 'nope'?
We all hung out

00:07:39.920 --> 00:07:42.630
at the same mixer that the
soccer club held last week!

00:07:42.710 --> 00:07:46.470
Oh right, I remember
going there! Who're you?

00:07:46.550 --> 00:07:48.800
[ALL]
You forgot about us already?

00:07:48.880 --> 00:07:49.930
Sasamoto!

00:07:50.010 --> 00:07:51.180
Kawakami!

00:07:51.260 --> 00:07:53.510
Hamada!

00:07:53.600 --> 00:07:56.350
[NARRATOR] Don't bother
memorizing those names.

00:07:56.430 --> 00:07:57.600
What the heck?

00:07:57.690 --> 00:07:59.230
I only went because
they begged me

00:07:59.310 --> 00:08:00.650
to go to help with the numbers.

00:08:00.730 --> 00:08:03.980
Yeah? So did you end up
running off with all the girls?

00:08:04.070 --> 00:08:06.900
No, way. We split up
at the train station.

00:08:06.990 --> 00:08:09.990
[SASAMOTO] Oh, is that it?
Then get your ass over here.

00:08:10.070 --> 00:08:13.160
Come be sad with us at our
consolation afterparty!

00:08:13.240 --> 00:08:14.700
[SAKAKI]
I don't know.

00:08:14.790 --> 00:08:18.040
I mean, you don't make it
sound very tempting.

00:08:18.120 --> 00:08:20.670
Besides, if you struck out,
it's probably on you.

00:08:20.750 --> 00:08:21.920
[SASAMOTO groans]

00:08:22.000 --> 00:08:23.500
Did you even make any
effort to accommodate

00:08:23.590 --> 00:08:24.800
the ladies that were there?

00:08:24.880 --> 00:08:26.170
[KAWAKAMI groans]

00:08:26.260 --> 00:08:27.840
Cause you do need to actually
let the other person

00:08:27.920 --> 00:08:29.680
talk when you're
having a conversation.

00:08:29.760 --> 00:08:32.010
[HAMADA screaming]

00:08:33.390 --> 00:08:34.640
[ALL crying]

00:08:34.720 --> 00:08:36.220
[SAKAKI] Apparently all that
bragging about your

00:08:36.310 --> 00:08:38.230
silly little club
bored them to tears.

00:08:38.310 --> 00:08:40.020
[GROUP]
Okay, we get it!

00:08:40.100 --> 00:08:41.650
[ASAI]
His words cut deep.

00:08:41.730 --> 00:08:43.860
[UZAKI]
Who knew he could be so savage?

00:08:43.940 --> 00:08:45.980
That guy sure roasts my nut.

00:08:46.070 --> 00:08:49.360
I can't believe we got schooled
so hard by such an average joe!

00:08:49.450 --> 00:08:51.820
And yet as soon as I said
Sakaki would be there

00:08:51.910 --> 00:08:54.080
suddenly the hotties
showed up real fast!

00:08:54.160 --> 00:08:58.370
But the worst thing is the way
you're flaunting those cuties!

00:08:58.460 --> 00:09:00.410
[KAWAKAMI]
Both of them are total babes!

00:09:00.500 --> 00:09:02.500
[HAMADA]
It isn't fair, bro!

00:09:02.580 --> 00:09:05.750
See, it's not great when
you say that stuff out loud.

00:09:05.840 --> 00:09:09.170
But it's totally okay
when you're doing it?

00:09:09.260 --> 00:09:12.260
Let's duke it out!
We'll go for 20 minutes.

00:09:12.340 --> 00:09:15.010
If you win, then your
time here today's on us,

00:09:15.100 --> 00:09:17.850
but if we defeat you...

00:09:17.930 --> 00:09:20.480
Uh, well, we'd
really appreciate it

00:09:20.560 --> 00:09:22.940
if you'd introduced us
to your friends.

00:09:23.020 --> 00:09:25.190
[ASAI]
What? Is that it?

00:09:25.270 --> 00:09:27.940
Oki-doke. The pipsqueak
is off limits,

00:09:28.030 --> 00:09:29.820
but you can try your
luck with the other.

00:09:29.900 --> 00:09:31.030
[GROUP]
Okay!

00:09:31.110 --> 00:09:32.910
[UZAKI, ASAI]
Huh?!

00:09:32.990 --> 00:09:34.410
What a rotten deal!

00:09:34.490 --> 00:09:35.620
Who ya callin' pipsqueak?

00:09:35.700 --> 00:09:38.240
Wait, what am I,
chopped liver or somethin'?

00:09:38.330 --> 00:09:41.330
Actually, you two can
just sit back and relax.

00:09:41.410 --> 00:09:44.040
We'll recruit a middle-schooler
for our goalie.

00:09:44.130 --> 00:09:48.340
[SAKAKI] It'll be fine. I got
a few tricks up my sleeve.

00:09:53.970 --> 00:09:55.510
[BOYS]
So cool!

00:09:55.600 --> 00:09:57.260
Just a few tricks, eh?

00:09:57.350 --> 00:10:01.230
So that's why he was so
quick to take up that bet.

00:10:01.310 --> 00:10:03.690
And then there's Sakurai.

00:10:03.770 --> 00:10:04.810
[laughs]

00:10:04.900 --> 00:10:06.360
What're you doin', slowpoke?

00:10:06.440 --> 00:10:09.650
Wake up those legs
and kick that ball!

00:10:11.280 --> 00:10:12.530
[UZAKI]
Keep it up big guy!

00:10:12.610 --> 00:10:14.150
You're killing it out there!

00:10:14.240 --> 00:10:17.740
[ASAI] This game sure brings out
the cheerleader in you, huh?

00:10:17.830 --> 00:10:22.000
[SASAMOTO] Sakaki's incredible.
Why didn't he join the club?

00:10:22.080 --> 00:10:23.710
This dude is somethin' else.

00:10:23.790 --> 00:10:26.500
He's really starting to get
on my nerves, the prick.

00:10:26.580 --> 00:10:27.420
Hold on.

00:10:27.500 --> 00:10:28.840
Stop laughing at me...

00:10:28.920 --> 00:10:31.880
[SASAMOTO] They've got a
weakness. Take him down first.

00:10:31.970 --> 00:10:34.630
We gotta score at
least once before it's over!

00:10:34.720 --> 00:10:37.640
Even if we lose, we can
do that much, right?

00:10:37.720 --> 00:10:39.510
We're so done.

00:10:41.270 --> 00:10:42.310
[SAKAKI]
Saku.

00:10:42.390 --> 00:10:43.640
[SAKURAI]
Hm?

00:10:43.730 --> 00:10:46.270
We're up by quite a bit,
so you can relax.

00:10:46.350 --> 00:10:48.650
I appreciate it, but
I've barely even helped.

00:10:48.730 --> 00:10:50.230
