with those legs of yours.

00:10:53.320 --> 00:10:54.650
If the ball comes your way,

00:10:54.740 --> 00:10:57.320
just keep running and kick
it towards the goal, okay?

00:10:57.410 --> 00:11:00.330
Copy that.

00:11:00.410 --> 00:11:04.500
[SAKURAI] That's right.
Don't think about it.

00:11:04.580 --> 00:11:08.590
All you have to do is
concentrate on the goal.

00:11:09.960 --> 00:11:12.210
[SAKURAI]
Yes, focus.

00:11:12.300 --> 00:11:15.090
Don't get distracted
by anything else.

00:11:16.260 --> 00:11:19.350
[SAKURAI]
Keep your eyes on the ball!

00:11:19.430 --> 00:11:22.680
[UZAKI]
Hm? Sakurai's face...

00:11:22.770 --> 00:11:26.390
It looks...

00:11:26.480 --> 00:11:28.730
...like it did in high school.

00:11:28.810 --> 00:11:30.230
[gasps]

00:11:35.570 --> 00:11:36.570
[SAKAKI]
Here it comes!

00:11:36.650 --> 00:11:38.450
That ball is mine!

00:11:38.530 --> 00:11:41.870
[SAKURAI]
Now's your chance. Go time!

00:11:41.950 --> 00:11:43.330
[SAKAKI]
Do it!

00:11:43.410 --> 00:11:47.540
[SAKURAI yelling]

00:11:47.620 --> 00:11:48.670
[SASAMOTO gasps]

00:11:56.380 --> 00:11:58.090
[SAKURAI growls]

00:12:00.600 --> 00:12:03.760
[SAKURAI]
Wind back... and kick!

00:12:03.850 --> 00:12:05.560
[ASAI gasping]

00:12:05.640 --> 00:12:07.390
[KAWAKAMI gasping]

00:12:11.270 --> 00:12:12.360
[SAKURAI]
Last one!

00:12:12.440 --> 00:12:13.730
[HAMADA gasping]

00:12:16.400 --> 00:12:18.610
[HAMADA groans]

00:12:21.830 --> 00:12:24.580
[SAKURAI panting]

00:12:27.290 --> 00:12:31.960
I did it. Goal! [laughs]

00:12:32.040 --> 00:12:33.420
Huh?

00:12:47.730 --> 00:12:50.600
Right. Run for your life!

00:12:50.690 --> 00:12:52.360
[GROUP]
Huh?!

00:12:52.440 --> 00:12:53.770
[SAKAKI]
You kids can go home now!

00:12:53.860 --> 00:12:55.770
[ALL]
Aw!

00:12:55.860 --> 00:12:57.110
You sure about this, man?

00:12:57.190 --> 00:12:59.610
About what? We won,
so it's time to go home!

00:12:59.700 --> 00:13:01.200
Don't you think
giving concussions

00:13:01.280 --> 00:13:02.870
to the other team was overkill?

00:13:02.950 --> 00:13:04.990
Hey, that was a coincidence!

00:13:05.080 --> 00:13:06.410
[STUDENT C]
That was amazing.

00:13:06.490 --> 00:13:07.830
[STUDENT D]
Right?

00:13:07.910 --> 00:13:10.580
[STUDENT A] That guy's a beast--
a god of destruction!

00:13:10.660 --> 00:13:12.130
[SAKURAI growls]

00:13:12.210 --> 00:13:14.170
[NARRATOR] And thus,
before he even knew it,

00:13:14.250 --> 00:13:18.300
Sakurai became a minor legend
of the local futsal court.

00:13:18.380 --> 00:13:20.920
[ASAI] Sure nothing "steamy"
went down back there,

00:13:21.010 --> 00:13:24.550
but it was still a hot
day on the field! [laughs]

00:13:29.480 --> 00:13:32.020
[UZAKI]
Wow, you went all out, huh?

00:13:32.100 --> 00:13:33.230
[SAKURAI]
Sure did!

00:13:33.310 --> 00:13:34.940
I got pretty good at making udon

00:13:35.020 --> 00:13:37.900
after your mom
gave us that lesson.

00:13:37.980 --> 00:13:40.570
[UZAKI] She's been looking
forward to trying yours out.

00:13:40.650 --> 00:13:43.320
[TEEN B]
Wait! Slow down, will you?

00:13:43.410 --> 00:13:45.580
If we don't hurry, we're
gonna be late, dummy!

00:13:45.660 --> 00:13:46.990
[UZAKI]
Huh?

00:13:52.580 --> 00:13:54.170
[UZAKI]
What's up, Sakurai!

00:13:54.250 --> 00:13:55.380
[growls]

00:13:55.460 --> 00:13:57.960
Why the awful expression
this morning?

00:13:58.050 --> 00:13:59.800
You always make it
point to start

00:13:59.880 --> 00:14:01.970
the day off looking
that miserable?

00:14:02.050 --> 00:14:03.760
Cause that mug of yours
is giving off

00:14:03.840 --> 00:14:06.390
an especially
villainous vibe today!

00:14:06.470 --> 00:14:09.140
The world's most
annoying upperclassman.

00:14:09.220 --> 00:14:11.850
I see you continue to be
as irritating as ever.

00:14:11.930 --> 00:14:13.100
What was that?

00:14:13.190 --> 00:14:15.440
Are you trying to be
funny, big guy?

00:14:15.520 --> 00:14:16.980
[UZAKI]
So frickin' rude!

00:14:17.070 --> 00:14:21.150
And here I am looking out for my
miserable loner of a friend.

00:14:21.240 --> 00:14:23.400
Are you aware that your
ungrateful behavior

00:14:23.490 --> 00:14:25.240
is a deeply inappropriate
way to treat

00:14:25.320 --> 00:14:27.160
your considerate and
beautiful classmate?

00:14:27.240 --> 00:14:29.830
So? I never asked for your help.

00:14:29.910 --> 00:14:32.040
All the more reason
to act grateful.

00:14:32.120 --> 00:14:34.670
You're getting affection from
the kindness of my heart!

00:14:34.750 --> 00:14:37.710
Is it kindness when you're
demanding something in return?

00:14:37.790 --> 00:14:40.000
Ha! Do you know
how petty you sound

00:14:40.090 --> 00:14:43.340
sweating over details like that?
You and your meathead brain,

00:14:43.420 --> 00:14:45.470
always trying to think
of ways to trip me up!

00:14:45.550 --> 00:14:47.550
Really? Do you know
how you sound

00:14:47.640 --> 00:14:50.970
gabbing away like your speech
center's made of Swiss cheese?

00:14:51.060 --> 00:14:53.480
You and your big mouth,
always open.

00:14:53.560 --> 00:14:54.690
Watch your tongue!

00:14:54.770 --> 00:14:56.860
Yeah, okay. Whatever.

00:14:56.940 --> 00:14:58.360
What do you want me
to say instead?

00:14:58.440 --> 00:15:01.690
That you might be built small,
but your heart's real big?

00:15:01.780 --> 00:15:04.650
Guess you're right, I should
be more grateful, huh?

00:15:04.740 --> 00:15:08.070
All right, enough trash talk!
It's punishment time!

00:15:08.160 --> 00:15:09.490
Wha--

00:15:09.580 --> 00:15:12.000
How many times have I told
you to lay off my height?

00:15:12.080 --> 00:15:13.500
Hey, you're choking me.

00:15:13.580 --> 00:15:15.040
You don't get to boss me around

00:15:15.120 --> 00:15:17.210
just because you've got
a few inches on me!

00:15:17.290 --> 00:15:19.170
Wait, I need to
tell you something!

00:15:19.250 --> 00:15:21.750
If you're trying to apologize,
it's too late!

00:15:21.840 --> 00:15:24.300
Actually, it's way more urgent.

00:15:24.380 --> 00:15:26.550
Then quit crying and
spit it out already!

00:15:26.630 --> 00:15:28.300
It's just that you're
kinda rubbing up

00:15:28.390 --> 00:15:30.600
against my face a little.

00:15:30.680 --> 00:15:32.470
[UZAKI screaming]

00:15:32.560 --> 00:15:36.390
Who's to say I'm not doing it on
purpose? Maybe I'm being nice!

00:15:36.480 --> 00:15:38.150
What, you can't handle
gettin' a little love

00:15:38.230 --> 00:15:39.860
from your ol' pal Uzaki?

00:15:39.940 --> 00:15:41.400
[SAKURAI]
I don't understand,

00:15:41.480 --> 00:15:44.190
are you punishing me or are
you showing me affection?

00:15:44.280 --> 00:15:46.150
Make up your mind!

00:15:46.240 --> 00:15:47.530
[UZAKI]
Shut up and take it!

00:15:47.610 --> 00:15:49.030
[SAKURAI screams]

00:15:49.120 --> 00:15:51.490
[NARRATOR]
Both options were the same.

00:15:51.580 --> 00:15:54.200
[SAKURAI]
You good? You're blushing.

00:15:54.290 --> 00:15:55.540
[gasping]

00:15:55.620 --> 00:15:59.080
No, I am not. Quit being
so annoying! Just drop it!

00:15:59.170 --> 00:16:01.290
[SAKURAI]
Uh, all right?

00:16:01.380 --> 00:16:05.050
C'mon, my mom's waiting
for us, so let's get going!

00:16:05.130 --> 00:16:06.510
'Kay.

00:16:07.840 --> 00:16:09.390
[slurping]

00:16:10.760 --> 00:16:13.430
Nice work.
They came out delicious!

00:16:13.510 --> 00:16:14.890
Glad to hear it.

00:16:14.970 --> 00:16:16.850
Seriously, if you
keep working at it,

00:16:16.930 --> 00:16:19.980
you could be a master
chef someday, Sakurai!

00:16:20.060 --> 00:16:21.610
Nah, I'm a scrub.

00:16:21.690 --> 00:16:25.990
See, I've only made udon.
I brought the extras, too.

00:16:26.070 --> 00:16:28.070
[TSUKI]
That's a ton!

00:16:28.150 --> 00:16:31.070
At some point it became way
more fun to make than eat.

00:16:31.160 --> 00:16:33.830
Well, I suppose when there's
a will there's a way, right?

00:16:33.910 --> 00:16:35.330
You were able to
train yourself by

00:16:35.410 --> 00:16:38.040
focusing solely
on a single recipe.

00:16:38.120 --> 00:16:39.420
U-don't say!

00:16:39.500 --> 00:16:42.130
Knock it off with
the dad jokes, you!

00:16:42.210 --> 00:16:43.840
I am getting sick
of noodles though,

00:16:43.920 --> 00:16:45.750
so I was maybe wondering
if you wouldn't mind

00:16:45.840 --> 00:16:47.590
teaching me how to
make something else?

00:16:47.670 --> 00:16:49.220
It would be my pleasure.

00:16:49.300 --> 00:16:52.800
Hold up, you can't move
on to another dish yet!

00:16:52.890 --> 00:16:55.100
Huh? And why would that be?

00:16:55.180 --> 00:16:57.230
Huh? You don't know the reason?

00:16:57.310 --> 00:16:59.390
I mean I could tell you, but
I don't think you're ready.

00:16:59.480 --> 00:17:02.110
[SAKURAI]
Ugh, just spit it out!

00:17:02.190 --> 00:17:03.900
[UZAKI]
Look, see this?

00:17:03.980 --> 00:17:06.480
No matter how well
you knead your dough,

00:17:06.570 --> 00:17:08.530
if you cut it wrong,
it's ruined.

00:17:08.610 --> 00:17:11.240
They need to be sliced to the
same thickness so they all

00:17:11.320 --> 00:17:15.540
finish cooking at the
exact same time, duh!

00:17:15.620 --> 00:17:19.250
These noodles are defective, and
I declare them unfit for eating!

00:17:19.330 --> 00:17:21.790
[SAKURAI yelling]

00:17:23.630 --> 00:17:25.090
[TSUKI]
As you stuff your face...

00:17:25.170 --> 00:17:27.300
Are you starting to
get the picture now?

00:17:27.380 --> 00:17:29.380
You can't call yourself
an udon master

00:17:29.470 --> 00:17:31.260
if this is the garbage
you're cranking out!

00:17:31.340 --> 00:17:33.260
You sorry amateur!

00:17:33.350 --> 00:17:35.560
[TSUKI] Why is she talking
down to him like that?

00:17:35.640 --> 00:17:38.020
Weren't they supposed
to be friends?

00:17:38.100 --> 00:17:42.390
You're absolutely right. I can't
move on till these are perfect.

00:17:42.480 --> 00:17:46.230
I must learn. Please teach me
the right knife technique.

00:17:46.320 --> 00:17:48.190
That's more like it, chef!

00:17:48.280 --> 00:17:49.820
[TSUKI]
I'm happy to.

00:17:49.900 --> 00:17:52.950
But in the meantime, won't you
end up getting even more

00:17:53.030 --> 00:17:55.330
sick of noodles than
you already are now?

00:17:55.410 --> 00:17:56.620
U-don't even know!

00:17:56.700 --> 00:17:58.910
Enough food puns!

00:18:01.290 --> 00:18:04.040
Show me how you
usually cut them.

00:18:05.290 --> 00:18:06.420
[TSUKI]
Ah, I see.

00:18:06.500 --> 00:18:07.840
[SAKURAI]
Huh?

00:18:07.920 --> 00:18:10.800
Can you try taking a step back
on your right-hand side?

00:18:10.880 --> 00:18:12.130
[SAKURAI]
Like this?

00:18:12.220 --> 00:18:14.130
[TSUKI]
Maybe a little more like this...

00:18:14.220 --> 00:18:15.930
[TSUKI gasps]

00:18:16.010 --> 00:18:19.930
Oopsie! Sorry about that, dear.
I got in your personal bubble!

00:18:20.020 --> 00:18:21.350
[TSUKI]
This isn't good.

00:18:21.430 --> 00:18:25.360
I totally forgot, Sakurai
may be Hana's boyfriend,

00:18:25.440 --> 00:18:29.530
but he also has dangerous
designs for her mother. For me!

00:18:29.610 --> 00:18:32.360
[NARRATOR]
Tsuki Uzaki, 43 years of age,

00:18:32.440 --> 00:18:36.070
had magnificently
misread the situation.

00:18:36.870 --> 00:18:39.910
[gasping]

00:18:39.990 --> 00:18:42.870
[UZAKI]
Look at him concentrate.

00:18:42.960 --> 00:18:45.330
Sakurai throws himself
into whatever he does

00:18:45.420 --> 00:18:47.500
and gets right into the zone.

00:18:47.590 --> 00:18:49.630
He doesn't react to anything
when he's like this,

00:18:49.710 --> 00:18:51.510
which is great for pranking him.

00:18:51.590 --> 00:18:53.220
[TSUKI]
He doesn't?

00:18:56.680 --> 00:18:57.970
[UZAKI]
Aw, what a shame.

00:18:58.050 --> 00:19:01.060
This would've been the
perfect opportunity, too.

00:19:01.140 --> 00:19:03.850
[TSUKI]
W-Would it?

00:19:03.930 --> 00:19:06.560
[UZAKI]
C'mon, let's go sit.

00:19:06.650 --> 00:19:08.900
[TSUKI]
Right. Now's my chance!

00:19:08.980 --> 00:19:12.530
I must mend this messed-up
relationship at once!

00:19:13.990 --> 00:19:16.070
[NARRATOR]
Little did Tsuki Uzaki know,

00:19:16.160 --> 00:19:18.990
she was the one
who was "messed up."

00:19:19.080 --> 00:19:20.870
[TSUKI]
Say, Hana?

00:19:20.950 --> 00:19:22.410
[UZAKI]
Huh?

00:19:22.490 --> 00:19:26.830
[TSUKI] I'll start with her.
I should go about this gently.

00:19:26.920 --> 00:19:28.210
I was wondering,

00:19:28.290 --> 00:19:31.550
how have things been between
you and Sakurai lately?

00:19:31.630 --> 00:19:32.760
What does that mean?

00:19:32.840 --> 00:19:34.760
Oh, nothing in particular.

00:19:34.840 --> 00:19:37.470
Why, has something
unusual happened?

00:19:37.550 --> 00:19:38.600
[UZAKI]
Hm?

00:19:40.140 --> 00:19:43.390
[gasping]

00:19:43.470 --> 00:19:44.430
[UZAKI whimpering]

00:19:44.520 --> 00:19:46.140
[SAKAKI]
Oop, Uzaki woke up first.

00:19:46.230 --> 00:19:48.690
[ITO] I'll send you the
pictures later, okay, Hana?

00:19:48.770 --> 00:19:51.020
Ohh, or do you prefer
video instead?

00:19:51.110 --> 00:19:53.320
Oh no, this is embarrassing!

00:19:53.400 --> 00:19:56.740
Wake up and let go of me
already, you big stupid weirdo!

00:19:56.820 --> 00:19:58.320
[SAKURAI grumbles]

00:20:00.200 --> 00:20:03.490
[NARRATOR] A collision of
two separate coincidences.

00:20:03.580 --> 00:20:05.450
The daughter,
who wondered how Mom

00:20:05.540 --> 00:20:07.750
found out about
that slumber party.

00:20:07.830 --> 00:20:09.670
And the mother,
who for better or worse,

00:20:09.750 --> 00:20:13.090
happened to be prying
for something else.

00:20:13.170 --> 00:20:17.800
[UZAKI]
But how? Who told her?

00:20:17.880 --> 00:20:19.590
Have you seen these yet?

00:20:19.680 --> 00:20:22.850
[CAFÉ OWNER] Mm?
You won't believe what I heard.

00:20:22.930 --> 00:20:25.850
[ASAI gasps]
Ma'am, you gotta see this!

00:20:25.930 --> 00:20:28.060
[UZAKI]
Is that how she found out?

00:20:28.140 --> 00:20:31.270
[NARRATOR] It was a sad
chain of misunderstandings.

00:20:31.360 --> 00:20:37.650
[exhales] What could I do?
It's just a habit of his.

00:20:37.740 --> 00:20:41.870
[TSUKI]
A habit, as in a fetish?

00:20:41.950 --> 00:20:45.120
We probably shouldn't have let
anyone at school see us, though.

00:20:45.200 --> 00:20:47.410
[TSUKI]
See them? At school?

00:20:47.500 --> 00:20:49.750
[UZAKI]
Plus, it's all on video, too.

00:20:49.830 --> 00:20:51.710
[TSUKI]
They recorded it?

00:20:51.790 --> 00:20:55.010
I-I tried to get up, but
Sakurai just wouldn't let me go.

00:20:55.090 --> 00:20:57.010
[TSUKI]
One round wasn't enough?

00:20:57.090 --> 00:21:01.090
And it was such a big mess.
Big mess... Big mess...

00:21:01.180 --> 00:21:04.180
[TSUKI] I can't believe they've
already taken things that far.

00:21:04.260 --> 00:21:06.850
If only I'd been
more strict with her..

00:21:06.930 --> 00:21:09.350
...this never would
have happened!

00:21:11.230 --> 00:21:16.320
[TSUKI] Hana, I'm going to go
lie down now. Mommy's tired.

00:21:16.400 --> 00:21:19.650
Okay, have a good nap.

00:21:19.740 --> 00:21:22.530
[NARRATOR] Having hurt only
herself with her delusions,

00:21:22.620 --> 00:21:27.660
Tsuki Uzaki's days of anguish
would continue a bit longer.

00:21:27.750 --> 00:21:30.460
[sighs] I did it.

00:21:30.540 --> 00:21:33.420
[NARRATOR] The noodles
were perfectly sliced.

00:21:37.710 --> 00:21:40.630
Aw nuts, not udon
for dinner again!

00:21:40.720 --> 00:21:43.720
Yeah, one of my friends
made way too much.

00:21:43.800 --> 00:21:46.930
Wait one of your friends
nooded up these noods?

00:21:53.190 --> 00:21:55.820
Ha, don't mind if I do then!

00:21:55.900 --> 00:21:57.480
[NARRATOR]
And just like that,

00:21:57.570 --> 00:22:00.530
another misunderstanding
was born.

00:22:00.610 --> 00:22:04.370
[KIRI] Meals prepared by college
girls are the freakin' best!

00:22:04.450 --> 00:22:06.490
[UZAKI]
Wow, he's hungry.

00:22:06.580 --> 00:22:07.740
[YANAGI]
I'm home!

00:22:07.830 --> 00:22:10.620
[UZAKI]
Uh? Hey, Yanagi.